question: Portugal Legislative Election: Will the Socialist Party win the most votes?
description:
Snap legislative elections are scheduled to take place on March 10, 2024 to elect members of the Assembly of the Republic (Assembleia da República) to the 16th Legislature of Portugal (XVI Legislatura da Terceira República Portuguesa). All 230 seats to the Assembly of the Republic are up for election.

This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Socialist Party (Partido Socialista, PS) wins the most votes in the 2024 Portuguese legislative elections. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from the Portuguese government and/or information published through the official website of the National Elections Commission (Comissão Nacional de Eleições, CNE): https://www.cne.pt/content/eleicoes-referendos. However, a consensus of credible media reports will also suffice to resolve this market.

question: Will Biden say "Trump" during his State of the Union address?
description:
Note: Be aware that State of the Union prepared remarks are oftentimes released before the speech starts.

This market will resolve to "Yes" if Biden says "Trump" or "trump" during his State of the Union address, scheduled to take place on March 7, 2024. Otherwise, the market will resolve to "No."

This market's primary resolution source is live video of the SOTU available here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nFVUPAEF-sw. Only in the event of ambiguity may the official transcript and other credible sources be considered.

Pluralization/possessive of the words will count toward the resolution of this market.

Any mention of the listed word, regardless of the context of its usage, will count towards the resolution of this market. E.g. if Biden says "I have a trump card up my sleeve" this market will resolve to "Yes."

If the State of the Union does not take place by March 8, 2024 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to "No".

question: tremp vs. boden - Most Liked Post Today
description:
This is a market on whether doland tremp (https://twitter.com/dolandtremp_sol) or im boden (https://twitter.com/bodenonsolana) will have the most liked post made on March 7.

This market will resolve to "$tremp" if @dolandtremp_sol has the most liked post on March 7. 
This market will resolve to "$boden" if @bodenonsolana has the most liked post on March 7.
This market will resolve to 50-50 if they are tied (for example if both Tremp's and Boden's most liked post shows 2.1k likes, this market will resolve to 50-50).

For the purposes of resolving this market, only main feed posts (including quote posts) will count. Replies and reposts will NOT count for this market's resolution, in addition to posts deleted before March 8, 2024, 12:00 AM ET. 

The resolution for this market will be based on checking the most liked post made by each account between March 7, 2024, 12:00 AM ET (inclusive) and March 7, 2024 11:59 PM ET (inclusive) at precisely March 8, 2024, 12:00 AM ET. If upon check at resolution time, one of the accounts has no posts on March 7 or was banned/deleted, this market will resolve to the other account. If both have no posts/were banned/deleted, this market resolves 50-50.

Likes will be determined based on their appearance on X's desktop interface in English ET, as shown at the time of assessment, including any rounding shown. More granular numbers using different languages/regions will NOT be considered.

The resolution source for this market will be the 30-min candlestick high prices from Binance (https://www.binance.com/en/trade/BTC_USDT). If Binance is unavailable, a consensus of other credible sources will be used.

question: Will Ethereum hit $15k in 2024?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Ethereum (ETH) reaches a price of 15,000 or greater according to Binance by December 31, 2024, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

The resolution source for this market will be the 30-min candlestick high prices from Binance (https://www.binance.com/en/trade/ETH_USDT). If Binance is unavailable, a consensus of other credible sources will be used.

Note: If it is clear there is a large data discrepancy issue with Binance (e.g. ETH only hit 10k on other exchanges but 15k on Binance), a consensus of other credible sources may be used.

question: Solana ETF approved in 2024?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if any spot Solana ETF receives approval from the SEC by December 31, 2024, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

The primary resolution source for this market will be information from the SEC, however a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.
